<br>
Well, for the moment, I can out meatsheild the ground flopper, and soon enough, (I'm only lvl 20), I can flop too.  Yeah, the guy with 90 weight units of crafted can take more damage than I can, but only, and I do mean only, I can get the mobs attention from the beginning and keep it, permanently. Between my sword, my taunt skill, my DOTs, my debuffs, my taps, well, I think everyone gets the idea. Perfect complement for the backstabbers, the healers, the nukers, and that poor monk who just got off 6 attacks before anyone else even moved. <br>
<br>
However, first and foremost, I am a puller. Only the monk can out do me there, and his advantage goes away when I get Feign Death. I'll be able to bring the mob of your choice, dotted, snared, and debuffed, and I'll give myself a 50% chance of being able to tie a pretty pink bow upon his head. <br>
<br>
As for the people I want about me when I'm doing this? Gimme a Paladin, and all we're missing between us is SoW and good DD spells. A rogue would be nice to have along, just so he can poke around inside the back, assuming me and the Paladins big ol' 2 handers aren't going the whole way through. An Enchanter to handle my mispulls, along with a Shaman to turn me, the Pally, and the Rogue into pure death machines. Lastly, I want a Wizard or a Mage behind me to push that shredded mob the rest of the way into the underworld. <br>
<br>
Unfortunately, there's rather a lack of Shadow Knights on Brell, or so it seems, and a whole lot of people don't seem to be aware of what we are, what we can do, and how best to work with us. Our Darkness DOTs especially seem to be a victim of this... Please folks, unless it's a situation too hairy to wait, please don't snare or root. It overwrites our DOTs, which have a snare effect anyway. This goes doubly to Magicians. I realize there's some places where you don't want to have to bother casting root, but earth pets aren't exactly the most group friendly. Not only do they overwrite an SK or Necro's abilities, a rooted creature just stands there and hits your tank an extra couple of times, as opposed to the snare/dotted one who doesn't have enough speed anymore to run away... or at least that's my pet peeve about groups. <br>
<br>
I've said enough, and can shutup now. =p <br>
